rComments: Bassett = awesome. He really cares about what he's teaching. Some people think his lectures are boring but he is totally engaging during office hours.

He is definately very knowledgable about his subject matter, and he tries to develop his own opinions through his lecture notes.  He may seem very communist, but the class is easy, and if you get the chance to know him, he is a very nice guy to be around. There is a lot to do and research for a level 100 class, but I encourage taking the class.

A very good lecturer, he clearly cares about the material (developing nations).  He is very empathetic if you visit him during office hours and his tests are very predictable if you've done the readings and gone to class. His lecture notes are vague, so attendance is a good idea.

Bassett's online notes are very general. This makes going to lecture a must. Also has pop quizzes in lecture. Discussion is necessary to go to because of attendance issues and turn-in assignments, but relates little to what is covered in lecture. Papers are video essays that are unnecessary, and the reading load is ridiculous - just dont bother.

Does anyone know an alternative spelling for "biased?" I think it'd have to be "Bassett." While not a bad guy, he discredits himself terribly with his anti-American propoganda and emphasis on problems brought to the world by the West. Class is also considerably more work than a freakin' 101 should be. Very easy conceptually, but forget the effort.

He is fine as a professor but the grading system for this class screws you over if you have a hard TA.  You don't need to read the books that is like 2 questions out of 40 on the tests, and most TA's send out summaries before the tests. Make sure you see the video's and go to the lectures that will have a video or a quiz and you'll be fine.

if you read the books and attend lecture, it should be fine... the teacher's opinions are valuable in that they may differ from yours, but he also does research in the ivory coast and has some authority to say that what our country is doing may be harmful to 3rd world countries
It was an easy class so that made him pretty likable in my opinion.

The entire semester was just him pushing his stupid liberal extremist ideas on the class.  He only knows his opinions and nothing more.  And he's completely Anti-American. He makes statements as if everything out of his mouth is the most profound thing ever said. And he's horribly boring.

I took this class as a Senior, and let me tell you, it was my fun class that semester.  It might be hard compared to a "blow off" class, but compared to BIOCHEM 350 this was a breeze.  The Professor has a very unique point of view, but that's what professors are for, at least in upper levels.
This class isn't a blow off class...so don't expect to passively stand by and get an A. He doesn't push his beliefs like some mention. He's an average professor...not horrible, not great.
Very liberal. Lectures are boring and he tries to fill time with worthless facts. If you give him what he wants to hear, the class is easy.
all he does is try and push his commie propaganda on students

Bassett has the heart in the right place, but he has no clue how economies work, nor does he understand anything beyond his own beliefs.  He passively tries to indoctrinate everyone with his borderline Marxist beliefs.  That said, he's a nice guy and picks good books for the class.

The class lacked focus and jumped all over the place. His anti-chief views did ****me off, but he does have a wealth of knowledge about the subjects he teaches. Even though he is very knowledgable, his lectures can get boring.

Prof. Bassett is one of the most intelligent, intriguing men I have ever met.  His lectures are incredibly interesting so make sure you go to class because he randomly gives pop quizes.  The TA's for this class are great too.  This class really opened my eyes to life outside suburban America.
Lots and lots of work

His lectures focus on his leftist, socialist, and anti-American/anti-western society views more than anything else.
Good lecturer, class is fairly easy.
